Bathurst burr
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:A noxious weed whose seeds, enclosed in hooked burrs, stick to wool; <i>Xanthium spinosum</i> and its fruit
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: AND 1853 f. the NSW town; W3. Cf biddy-bid(dy), biddy-burr, burr.
